      "Here's some real use cases where I struggle with this every day using rethinkdb (which I :heart:, thx y'all) -- super psyched it is slated for 1.13.\r\n\r\n```js\r\nvar purchasedCourseIds = [1,2,3]; // dynamic array loaded from somewhere\r\nr.table('courses').getAll.apply(r.table('courses'), purchasedCourseIds)\r\n```\r\n\r\nI think this could be written as:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nr.table('courses').getAll(r.args(purchasedCourseIds))\r\n```\r\n\r\nSimilarly, but a bit more complex:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nr.table('courses').getAll(courseIds).map(function(course) {\r\n  return course.merge({\r\n    sections: course('sectionIds').map(function(sectionId) {\r\n      return r.table('sections').get(sectionId);\r\n    })\r\n  });\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nRe-written as:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nr.table('courses').getAll(courseIds).map(function(course) {\r\n  return course.merge({\r\n    sections: r.table('sections').getAll(r.args(course('sectionIds')))\r\n  });\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nIs that right? If so, \127881"
